President Muhammadu Buhari has vowed to convince Nigerians that he wants the best for the country. Buhari made the remark while noting that the Northwest, Southwest, and Southeast needs progress. The president disclosed this during an interview on Arise Television on Thursday. Buhari also disclosed that he would return to his farm at the end of his presidency. According to Buhari: “I have never ever abandoned my farm, when I leave, I will go back and try to keep myself busy. “Before then, I will try to convince Nigerians that I mean well for them. “Visibly, we need progress in the Northwest, Southwest, Southeast. Right now, Northwest is troubled. “I hope Nigerians would be fair to me.” Four foreign bandits operating in Northwest Nigeria nabbed